BFN 

  [Text] ETA [Basque Fatherland and Liberty] is demanding 
between 10 and 15 million pesetas from businessmen and 
professionals in Guipuzcoa as payment of the revolutionary tax. 
This is what is reported today in LA VANGUARDIA. The newspaper 
says that the terrorist group is threatening Basque businessmen 
with reprisals should this latest attempt at extortion be 
reported to the police. The criminal organization says that it 
has complete personal data on these businessmen that will be 
used against them should they refuse to make payments. 

